{
  "texts": [
    "Suppose χ M = ↓σ O.",
    "First, we show M, O ⊩ ♢ ▷ χ, which implies ♢ ▷ χ M ⊇ ↓O by Persistence.",
    "Recall from § 2.4 that M, O ⊩ ♢ ▷ χ if ∀O ′ ⊆ O ∃σ ′: O ′ R ▷ σ ′ and M, σ ′ ⊩ χ.",
    "Given O ′ ⊆ O, let σ ′ = {⟨a ′, b ′ ⟩ | ⟨a ′, b ′ ⟩ ∈ σ O and ∃(a, b) ⊆ O ′: (a, b) ⊆ (a ′, b ′)}.",
    "Observe that σ ′ ̸ = ∅ and O ′ R ▷ σ ′."
  ]
}